CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 22, 1961, pg. 1 reads: "Badly Beaten - Mrs. Marie Baylor, of the 1800 block of Bedford Ave., was severely beaten, last week, according to police reports, when she asked Harmon Stevick, a downtown pedestrian: "Please buy a flower." Mrs. Baylor was representing Carter Chapel CME Church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Marie Baylor wearing houndstooth dress, hat with bow, and eyeglasses, holding canister and small flowers for Carter Chapel CME Church fundraising, posed in front of door with glass block sidelights
